(12)
SJ adjectives (Nominal Adjectives) – genki-da ‘fine-copula’:
a. HH: Ono-san-wa genki {desu./ de gozaimas-u.}
‘Ono is sick.’
b. SH: Ono-san wa o-genki {da./ de irassyar-u.}
c. NSH: No NSH form

(28)
a. Hanako-ga isya {da./desu.}
Hanako-Nom doctor copula (plain/polite)
‘Hanako is a doctor.’
b. Seito-ga sizuka {da./desu.}
Pupil-Nom quiet copula (plain/polite)
‘The pupils are quiet.’
c. * Sensei-ga sinbun-o yom-u {da./desu.}
teacher-Nom newspaper-Acc read copula (plain/polite)
‘The teacher read a newspaper.’
